y 9, 2014", "recommendations/1/description": "To whom it may concern;\n\nDuring Jonah's employment at Waldorf Astoria Shanghai Jonah led the entire Waldorf Food & Beverage Division and has always showed a balance of leadership, technical skills, process improvement and business acumen. \n\nJonah has a strong work ethic and drive & passion for quality and excellence.\n\nI do not hesitate to recommend Jonah to any future employer.\n\nBjorn Courage", "recommendations/1/name": "Jonah Roberman ", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Hospitality Executive | Luxury Hotels and Resorts | Multi-Asset P&L, Turnarounds, Pre-Openings | APAC & Global", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonahroberman/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJLv2kBHnXMqgHiU98KeAsJDx5PUntDQWY", "recommendations/2/context": "Bjorn worked with Alasdair on the same team", "recommendations/2/date": "December 13, 2011", "recommendations/2/description": "It is with delight to state my great appreciation and respect for Alasdair, with whom I had the pleasure to work between 2004 and 2005 as Area Director of Sales & Marketing Six Senses Thailand, during a time our business in Phuket (Thailand) was devastated by the Great 2004 Indian Ocean Tsunami. Alasdair showed incredible leadership by not only handling his most challenging operational responsibilities, but also his in-depth understanding of the importance and urgency to restructure our business module to not only initiate a speedy recovery but also obtain an improved overall market share position post crisis. Without a doubt Alasdair was instrumental in Evason Phuket’s strong and rapid recovery. His sales, marketing and business sense, his obvious exceptional operational qualities as well as his honest, determined and professional character will for sure take Alasdair’s career to new heights again and again.", "recommendations/2/name": "Alasdair Junor", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Managing Director at The Private office", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alasdairjunor/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJMYCQBL3qr_rwHEdeV10ZpZ5b--S8oJBM", "recommendations/3/context": "Bjorn was Adam's client", "recommendations/3/date": "February 17, 2011", "recommendations/3/description": "I have had the great pleasure of working with Adam Bruzzone and his dedicated team on two extensive photo shoot projects requiring both “product” as well as “image” shots.\n \nAdam has the rare ability as a photographer to not only understand the way the property is photographed best but also to understand and to work hand-in-hand with hotel management in order to ensure their expectations / views are fully integrated into the overall photo shoot without compromising the marketing purpose of the photo shoot nor disturbing the hotel operation in any way. His flexibility, originality and creativity in making a complex photo shoot as smooth as he does is very commendable, even if it takes extreme long days from him and his team. \n \nAdditionally his knowledge and experience of digital photography reassures any client that the best shots are guaranteed, unless uncontrollable elements such as weather decide to intervene. Also the fact that Adam offers the possibility to edit images during the shoot itself and hence is able to show the final images prior to his departure is a “priceless” service and reassures any client that the important images needed have been successfully obtained prior to Adam actual leaving the property, this has always been extremely important to me with so much at stake when committing to hiring an official external photographer.\n \nOverall it truly is refreshing to work with professionals like Adam whose expertise, professional attitude and dedication truly generate beautiful images which have always been generated in a very cooperative, understanding, energizing and cost-effective way, especially knowing that due to the new visuals incremental business was secured and ADR improvements were seen as soon as the new visuals were fully reflected on hotel website, hotel collateral, 3rd party travel websites, travel agent programs, etc. \n \nWithout a doubt that Adam and I will work together for many years to come and hence I would have no hesitation whatsoever in recommending him and his team", "recommendations/3/name": "Adam Bruzzone", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Managing Director at Adam Bruzzone Photography Pty. Ltd", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adambruzzone/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIMibIBEgDeXC2hEB-5vd4FNmd1V6sKZVg", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Jonah reported directly to Bjorn", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "March 22, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I worked with Bjorn at the Waldorf Astoria Shanghai. He was an impressive and effective leader, a committed Director and an engaged mentor. \n\nHe inspires enthusiasm and dedication in his staff. His calm, consistent and considerate approach to all things was felt by all of us who were fortunate to work under his leadership. We worked alongside one another on a number of projects and his guidance was invaluable. \n\nI have a great respect for him and wish him well in his new role as General Manager. I hope to work with him again one day. Thank you Bjorn, I appreciate your support and the dedication you offered our team.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Jonah Roberman ", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Hospitality Executive | Luxury Hotels and Resorts | Multi-Asset P&L, Turnarounds, Pre-Openings | APAC & Global", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonahroberman/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJLv2kBHnXMqgHiU98KeAsJDx5PUntDQWY", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Spencer was Bjorn's client", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "May 26, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Bjorn Courage is a pleasure to work with.  Every time we visit his facility he is sure to take good care of our team and our partners as well.  \n\nWith him in management, it is no wonder why his team has a good solid sense of customer service.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Spencer Wolfe", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Connect to your customers and team in APAC- CIRCLE Cloud Communications", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/spencerwolfe/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAA9PY4BHet0R8bEbWmgeiGALgF70pBfwIY", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Bjorn was Adam's client", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "February 21, 2011", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "I have had the pleasure of working as a consultant (advertising photographer) with Bjorn on 2 occasions to date.  In any major photography assignment the consultation process, brief and pre-production is paramount in completing a successful shoot with many powerful images.  These provide the hotels core advertising material and form the best first impression of the hotel and its brand that directly affects the emotional connection, and hence sales, with consumers. \n\nBjorn directed and understood all associated variables and contributed greatly to the success of these assignments.  He has a calm and personable character and such preparations were handled with style and ease. His courteous, fun, and generous manner powerfully augments a very strong and dedicated character.\n\n Even as a senior Director of considerable experience and respect within the industry he maintains ‘a hand’s on’ approach with his staff and any task at hand.  I noticed Bjorn to be extremely hard working and yet, with all of these talents above, is remarkably humble. In working closely with him it is also easy to notice he is well liked and highly respected by his colleagues, staff and associates.\n\nTo work with Bjorn is to work with a complete professional, a true hotelier and good human being; he is an inspiration in this manner.  I am delighted to work in partnership with Bjorn anytime and to regard him as a valued friend as well”.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Adam Bruzzone", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Managing Director at Adam Bruzzone Photography Pty. Ltd", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adambruzzone/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIMibIBEgDeXC2hEB-5vd4FNmd1V6sKZVg", "skills/0/title": "Revenue Analysis", "skills/1/title": "Hotels", "skills/2/title": "E-commerce", "skills/3/title": "Hospitality", "skills/4/title": "Business Development", "skills/5/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/6/title": "Resorts", "skills/7/title": "Public Relations", "skills/8/title": "Sales", "skills/9/title": "Marketing", "skills/10/title": "Rebranding", "totalExperienceYears": "29.7", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "4", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "3", "urn": "ACoAAAAK4lQBkJFwjfhl-cKlF0i2sCdTxputD50"}$$::jsonb),
